**Verified claims:**

1. **University of Illinois 2011 study** (Ariga & Lleras) — 50-min task, "switch" group took 2 brief diversions, showed no performance decline. CONFIRMED.
2. **2022 PLOS ONE meta-analysis** — 22 study samples, 2,335 participants, micro-breaks boosted vigor/reduced fatigue, exact quote matches. CONFIRMED.
3. **Journal of Health Psychology decision fatigue analysis** — describes procrastination, impulsivity, heuristic reliance, reduced executive function. CONFIRMED.
4. **PNAS Israeli judges study** (Danziger et al.) — 1,112 rulings, ~65% approval after breaks, dropping to near zero. CONFIRMED.
5. **2024 randomized crossover study** — 10-min breaks, healthcare workers, TMT-A: 56s outdoor vs 84s control (33% improvement). CONFIRMED.
6. **Cogent Engineering systematic review** — active micro-breaks of 2-3 min every 30 min, improved health, no productivity loss. CONFIRMED.
7. **University of Melbourne green roof study** — 40 seconds viewing green rooftop reduced attention errors vs concrete roof. CONFIRMED.
8. **DeskTime 52/17 finding** — most productive users worked ~52 min, broke for ~17 min. CONFIRMED.
9. **Box breathing / Navy SEALs** — activates parasympathetic nervous system, lowers cortisol. CONFIRMED.

All 8 source URLs are valid. Both internal links (`/blog/en/customize-pomodoro-intervals`, `/blog/en/why-multitasking-kills-productivity`) resolve to existing files. Pomodorian feature claims (ambient sounds, break reminders) are accurate. This is a very well-researched article.
